+# AI Expense Tracker Constitution
+
+## Principles
+
+### User Control
+
+Users own their financial data and must be able to review, edit, and delete
+records without depending on an AI provider.
+
+### Privacy By Default
+
+The application must not commit secrets, API keys, local databases, generated
+reports, or private receipts. Cloud AI integrations must remain optional.
+
+### Tested Financial Logic
+
+Changes to persistence, calculations, categorization, reports, and exports must
+include automated tests where practical.
+
+### Accessible Operation
+
+Core workflows must remain understandable without requiring technical knowledge
+or AI-specific configuration.
+
+### Automation First
+
+Quality checks, tests, static analysis, secret scanning, and dependency audits
+must be runnable in CI and through pre-commit hooks.
+
+## Governance
+
+This constitution guides feature specifications, plans, and review decisions.
+Changes require updating related specs, templates, and documentation.
