+# AI Expense Tracker
+
+AI Expense Tracker is a Streamlit application for tracking income, expenses,
+budgets, and financial trends. It combines a local SQLite database with optional
+AI providers so users can categorize spending, ask finance questions, generate
+reports, and parse receipt text.
+
+## Features
+
+- Add, view, update, and delete expenses and income records.
+- View dashboard metrics and Plotly charts for spending patterns.
+- Generate weekly and monthly reports from stored transactions.
+- Configure local Ollama or cloud AI providers such as OpenAI, Gemini, and
+  OpenRouter.
+- Parse receipt text and suggest expense categories.
+- Export reports as PDF files.
+
+## Tech Stack
+
+- Python 3.11
+- Streamlit
+- SQLAlchemy and SQLite
+- Pandas and NumPy
+- Plotly
+- Pytest and pytest-cov
+- Ruff, Mypy, Bandit, Semgrep, Vulture, Pylint, Flake8, and Pyupgrade
+
+## Installation
+
+```bash
+git clone https://code.swecha.org/Abdullah_285/expense-tracker.git
+cd expense-tracker
+python -m venv .venv
+.venv\Scripts\activate
+pip install -r requirements.txt
+```
+
+On Linux or macOS, activate the virtual environment with:
+
+```bash
+source .venv/bin/activate
+```
+
+## Configuration
+
+Copy the example environment file and add only the providers you plan to use:
+
+```bash
+cp .env.example .env
+```
+
+All AI integrations are optional. Ollama can run locally without an API key.
+Cloud providers require their own keys.
+
+## Usage
+
+```bash
+streamlit run app.py
+```
+
+Then open the local Streamlit URL shown in the terminal.
+
+## Testing And Quality
+
+Run the test suite:
+
+```bash
+pytest
+```
+
+Run the configured quality checks locally:
+
+```bash
+ruff check .
+ruff format --check .
+mypy .
+bandit -r .
+pip-audit
+```
+
+Pre-commit hooks are configured in `.pre-commit-config.yaml`.
+
+## Project Structure
+
+```text
+expense-tracker/
+├── app.py
+├── database/
+├── pages/
+├── services/
+├── tests/
+├── utils/
+├── .gitlab-ci.yml
+├── .pre-commit-config.yaml
+├── pyproject.toml
+├── requirements.txt
+└── README.md
+```
+
+## Documentation
+
+- `USER_MANUAL.md` explains the user workflow.
+- `CONTRIBUTING.md` explains contribution expectations.
+- `SECURITY.md` explains vulnerability reporting.
+- `AGENTS.md` gives guidance for automated contributors.
+- `specs/expense-tracker/spec.md` records the current product specification.
+
+## License
+
+This project is licensed under the GNU Affero General Public License v3.0.
+See `LICENSE` for details.
+
+## Author
+
+Developed by Md Abdullah.
