+# Feature Specification: AI Expense Tracker
+
+## Overview
+
+AI Expense Tracker helps users record income and expenses, understand spending
+patterns, generate financial reports, and optionally use AI providers for
+categorization and personal finance assistance.
+
+## User Stories
+
+- As a user, I can add income and expense records so my finances stay organized.
+- As a user, I can review dashboards and reports so I understand trends.
+- As a user, I can configure an AI provider so categorization and advice are
+  available when I choose to enable them.
+- As a privacy-conscious user, I can use the core tracker without cloud AI keys.
+
+## Functional Requirements
+
+- Store expenses, income, and settings in SQLite through SQLAlchemy models.
+- Display dashboard metrics and visualizations in Streamlit.
+- Provide pages for expenses, reports, AI assistant, and settings.
+- Support optional AI providers: Ollama, OpenAI, Gemini, and OpenRouter.
+- Parse receipt text into structured expense suggestions.
+- Generate PDF reports from financial data.
+
+## Quality Requirements
+
+- Run tests with Pytest and coverage reporting.
+- Run linting, formatting, type checking, static analysis, secret scanning, and
+  dependency audit in CI.
+- Keep API keys in environment variables and document them only in
+  `.env.example`.
+
+## Acceptance Criteria
+
+- A fresh clone can install dependencies from `requirements.txt`.
+- `streamlit run app.py` starts the application.
+- `pytest` runs the automated tests with a coverage threshold.
+- `.gitlab-ci.yml` runs quality, security, and test stages.
